"{\"uid\": \"wtam.iheart.com-content-2024-04-05-the-modern-day-olympic-games-begin-on-this-date-in-1896-in-greece\", \"text\": \"Today in1712, a\\u00a0slave revolt in New York saw six white men killed\\u00a0- and later, 21 African Americans executed.  Today in 1896,\\u00a0the first modern Olympic games\\u00a0began in Athens, Greece.  Today in 1909,\\u00a0explorers Robert E. Peary and Matthew A. Henson\\u00a0became the first men to reach the North Pole. The claim, disputed by skeptics, was upheld in 1989 by the Navigation Foundation.  Today in 1940,\\u00a0the new Civil Aeronautics Administration\\u00a0awarded honorary license number 1 to Orville Wright.  Today in 1985,\\u00a0William J. Schroeder\\u00a0became the first artificial heart recipient to be discharged from the hospital\\u00a0as he moved into an apartment in Louisville, Kentucky.  Today in 1996,accompanied by six children who survived the Oklahoma City bombing, President Clinton\\u00a0bowed his head in silent prayer at the site where 168 people were killed almost a year earlier.  Today in 1999,\\u00a0more than\\u00a0a decade after\\u00a0Pan Am\\u00a0Flight 103 exploded\\u00a0over\\u00a0Scotland - killing 270 people - the Libyan government bowed to years of diplomatic pressure and sanctions\\u00a0and handed over two suspects for trial.  Today in 2000,\\u00a0the father of Elian Gonzalez, Juan Miguel Gonzalez,\\u00a0arrived in the United States to press\\u00a0for the return of his six-year-old son to Cuba.  Today in 2009,\\u00a0a 6.3-magnitude earthquake\\u00a0struck near L'Aquila, Italy - killing more than 300, injuring more than one-thousand and displacing 65-thousand.  Today in 2016,\\u00a0the\\u00a0first baby conceived with DNA from three parents\\u00a0through mitochondrial transfer in Mexico was born. Because the procedure is not allowed in the United States, the child was conceived in Mexico, but born in New York.  \"}"